  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "<!-- Please only use this template for submitting enhancement requests -->\r\n\r\n**What would you like to be added**:\r\nCurrently cloud provider package aws.go has many places to query ec2 instance by node name. #76749 has already optimized quite few inefficient tagging usages in the library.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, since aws does not track ec2 instance by node name (node name is just a tag), querying instance by tag is not as efficient as querying instance by ID.\r\n\r\nIt will make k8s more efficient if k8s can convert nodeName to nodeID before actually making the cloud provider calls.\r\n\r\n**Why is this needed**:\r\nCurrently `Cloud` interface already have kubeClient exposed to it, we can get `v1.Node` from api call and parse providerID, and issue cloud provider call with providerID directly. We tried such optimization internally and it can tremendously reduce the number of DescribeInstance calls and also make each DescribeInstance call much faster.\r\n\r\nAlso, because node querying has limited frequency, mostly during node controller reconciliation, and the only bursts are during batch infrastructure provisioning (i.e. create a batch of 100 PVC with ebs), load added to api server is limited, and can be optimized further by introducing informer interface to aws cloud provider.\r\n\r\n/assign zhan849\r\n/sig aws\r\n/sig cloud-provider\r\n/sig scalability",
